{"lemma":"رَهْبانِيَّةُ","slug":"رَهْبانِيَّةُ","root":"ر.ه.ب","root_slug":"ر-ه-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ه-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَهْبانِيَّة","root":"رهب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16835"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"monasticism"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/rah.baː.nij.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16835","headword_ar":"رَهْبَانِيَّةٌ","root":"rhb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) written in an exposition of the Makámát [of El-Hareeree] without teshdeed, (Mgh,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Monkery; asceticism;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, of a monk"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ascetic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAhib","text_ar":"رَاهِب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Christian devotee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) the masdar of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAhibN","text_ar":"رَاهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahobapN","text_ar":"رَهْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or it is originally from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ahobapu","text_ar":"الرَّهْبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and by a secondary application is used as a noun signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extravagance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AAF, TA:) or it is from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahobanapN","text_ar":"رَهْبَنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which has the same signification, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolanapN","text_ar":"فَعْلَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahobapN","text_ar":"رَهْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolalapN","text_ar":"فَعْلَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the supposition that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a radical letter: (IAth, TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excess in religious services"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exercises, and discipline, and the detaching oneself from mankind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahobaAnu","text_ar":"رَهْبَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “excessively fearful:” so in the Kur lvii. 27; where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warahobaAniy~apF A@botadaEuwhaA","text_ar":"وَرَهْبَانِيَّةً ا@بْتَدَعُوهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@botadaEuwA rahobaAniy~apF A@botadaEuwhaA","text_ar":"وَا@بْتَدَعُوا رَهْبَانِيَّةً ا@بْتَدَعُوهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they innovated excess"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they innovated it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AAF, Bd, TA:) and some read with damm, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAniy~apF","text_ar":"رُهْبَانِيَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":",] as though from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAnN","text_ar":"رُهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAhibN","text_ar":"رَاهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Bd.) It is said in a trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA rahobaAniy~apa fiY","text_ar":"لَا رَهْبَانِيَّةَ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no monkery in El-Islám"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no such thing as the making oneself a eunuch, and putting chains upon one's neck, and wearing garments of hair-cloth, and abstaining from flesh-meat, and the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayokumo biA@lojihaAdi faA_in~ahu ruhobaAniy~apu A^um~atiY","text_ar":"عَلَيْكُمْ بِا@لْجِهَادِ فَاـِنَّهُ رُهْبَانِيَّةُ اُمَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep ye to the waging of war against the unbelievers, for it is the asceticism of my people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","Mgh","Msb","K","A","AAF","TA","IAth","Bd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}